Package edu.washington.cs.dm.jeremyc.netflix

Class Summary
Correlation A simple container for a co-occurence count, rating, entity type and entity IDs.
Correlation.CountSort This is used to pre-sort the correlations when applying a dynamic, cooccurence count threshold to the neighbors (we've used it to insist that the cooccurence is at least as large as the running average of cooccurences thus far, when sorting by descending cooccurences).
Correlation.TopCorrelators An ordered set of Correlations.
Correlation.WeightSort This is used to order the Correlations according to "nearness"
DualNNPredictor Uses a weighted average of Nearest Neighbor predictions along both dimensions (movie and user).
MemStore The in-memory store of the training data.
MemStore.Rating An ID rating pair.
MemStore.Ratings A simple wrapper around List<Rating> that caches the average of the rating values, and provides an init() method, called after the list is filled, to ensure the Rating list is sorted by ID and the average computed.
NNPredictor The basic implementation of nearest neighbor predictor, where either N nearest users or N nearest movies may be used for calculating predicted ratings.
Populator Reads the contents of a text file in the format provided for the project (e.g.
Populator.DataRow A simple container for a movieId, userId, rating triple.
Predictor The base class for all predictor implementations.
PredictorTester The main method for testing a predictor.
PredictorTester.PredictorHarness A simple container class.
 

Enum Summary
EntityType We make use of the duality of movie and user, and where logic is usable in both contexts, we use this enum to indicate which one we're using.
